statement.tex:
\text{For what value of k would }\\
f(x) = \begin{cases}
  kx + 1, x\leq 5, \\
  3x-5, x\gt 5
\end{cases}
\\ \text{be continuous at }x=5?

step.tex:
\begin{align}
  \lim_{x\to 5^-}f(x) &= \lim_{x\to 5^-}kx+1=5k + 1 \\
  \lim_{x\to 5^+}f(x) & \lim_{x\to 5^+}3x-5 = 10 \\
  f(5) &= 5k + 1
\end{align}
\\ \text{And hence, for continuity at }x=5 \\
\begin{align}
  5k + 1&= 10 \implies k = \dfrac{9}{5}
\end{align}
